flowRoot.flowPara: The primary purpose of a knowledge model is to be used to create a questionnaire that researchers fill in for their project (or to learn). Although the questionnaire can be very complex and contain even a few hundreds of questions, researchers won't be overwhelmed because only the relevant ones for the specific case will be shown based on the previous answers. Integrations, references, and advice are available to help with the answers. The questionnaire displays various indications including FAIR metrics. Answers are designed to be evaluated easily via various external integrated services within the DSW that we call evaluators.

To support efficient, smart, and straightforward work with data within research projects, an elaborate DMP is desirable. The DSW generates such a plan from the answered questionnaire using various templates and formats. Templates transform the answers into a DMP to fulfil various requirements of different organisations and to provide feedback to researchers. Aside from human-readable formats (PDF, DOCX, HTML, etc.), machine-actionable JSON is possible as well.

Data Management Plans (DMPs) are a crucial element of good data management and often required (e.g., H2020 projects). Adopting FAIR Data Principles is essential not just to satisfy the requirements of funders, but to benefit your research project too.

Knowledge models (KM) represent the data stewardship expertise using chapters, questions, possible answers, follow-up questions, advice, references, or integrations. Data stewards are the authors of captured knowledge and can build it from scratch (a new root KM) or customise an existing KM by adding, changing, or deleting some parts. This creates a tree hierarchies of the knowledge in the DSW which can be exported out, shared and imported again even in a different DSW instance.
Contains chapters, questions, answers, and related helpful information
Can be customised forming a tree hierarchies
Provides related information using references and integrations
Can be evaluated and its metrics (such as FAIR metrics) measured
Is generated from a filled questionnaire
Transforms answers using a selected template
Can be exported into many formats
